    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Release Ray's Report</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gregg Nelson letter says independent counsel Robert Ray should release his report on the Clintons before election, to better inform voters in New York, where Hillary Clinton is running for Senate (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Ray's Ill-Timed Report'' (editorial, Aug. 30):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mr. Ray's Ill-Timed Report'' (editorial, Aug. 30):</p>
        <p>You urge Robert W. Ray, the independent counsel investigating the Clintons, to delay the release of his report until after the election. That is exactly the wrong advice.</p>
        <p>If Hillary Rodham Clinton is innocent of any wrongdoing in Whitewater or other matters under investigation, then she has nothing to fear. But if she is found to have engaged in unethical behavior, what better time for voters to know this than upon entering the voting booth?</p>
        <p>GREGG NELSON  New York, Aug. 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
